===Talking to Garkor===
* '''Garkor:''' Have you learned anything from Awowogei yet?
* '''Player:''' He won't discuss his plans with anyone but his military commanders.
* '''Garkor:''' Ah, the monkey has more sense than we give him credit for... Perhaps you could go back in there as one of his commanders?
* '''Player:''' What do you mean?
* '''Garkor:''' Zooknock could get you disguised as one of Awowogei's commanders if you retrieved the necessary items for him to make a greegree. We just need to choose which commander to go after...
* '''Player:''' Well Awowogei mentioned something about a meeting with Kruk. He wanted me to go to find him.
* '''Garkor:''' Kruk eh... Captain of the monkey guard would certainly be a useful disguise to have at our disposal. Hopefully you can find him somewhere isolated from the rest of the guards... Once you have defeated him, take his
* '''Garkor:''' corpse to Zooknock along with an uncharged monkey talisman, well, you know the routine.
* '''Player:''' I'll get to it right away.
* {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Garkor again====
* '''Garkor:''' Have you learned anything from Awowogei yet?
* '''Player:''' I'm still working on getting that greegree.
* '''Garkor:''' Please hurry [player name], we need this information from Awowogei before it's too late.
* '''Player:''' I'll get to it right away.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Monkey Archer===
* '''Monkey Archer:''' What is it?
* '''Player:''' The king has sent me with a message for Kruk, any idea where I can find him?
* '''Monkey Archer:''' Your guess is as good as mine, you didn't hear it from me, but he's been disappearing from his post a lot lately...
* '''Monkey Archer:''' You might be able to track him down if you've got what it takes, although I wouldn't want to be the one caught sneaking up on Kruk!
* '''Player:''' Any idea where to start looking?
* '''Monkey Archer:''' There's only one way off the wall, and that's down the Western ramp to the shore. I know that's where I'd start looking.
* '''Player:''' Thanks.
* {{tact|end}}

====Talking to the Monkey Archer again====
* '''Monkey Archer:''' Any luck finding Kruk?
* '''Player:''' Not yet.
* '''Monkey Archer:''' You'd best not keep the king waiting, try tracking down Kruk's movements.
* '''Monkey Archer:''' There's only one way off the wall, and that's down the Western ramp to the shore. I know that's where I'd start looking.
* '''Player:''' Thanks.
* {{tact|end}}

===Confronting Kruk===
* '''Player:''' Stop right there, Kruk!
* '''Kruk:''' I'm impressed you made it so far, human.
* '''Kruk:''' However, I'm afraid that this is the end of the line for you.
* {{tact|end}}

====Using a banana on Kruk====
* '''Kruk:''' {{overhead|?}}

===Talking to Awowogei (as Kruk)===
* '''Awowogei:''' Ah finally, Kruk! I was beginning to think you had run into trouble...
* '''Player:''' Uh... No, everything is fine.
* '''Awowogei:''' Excellent. Have you had any further considerations for our plans?
* '''Player:''' And which plans would we be talking about here?
* '''Awowogei:''' Are you sure everything is okay Kruk? You seem very distracted lately.
* '''Player:''' I'm fine, just been very busy thinking over those plans. Could you remind me where we left off last time?
* '''Awowogei:''' We decided to move forward with our three-way assault.
* '''Awowogei:''' You were negotiating an alliance with the ogres and trolls, working on a new fleet of battleships and then developing that secret weapon of yours.
* '''Awowogei:''' So, how is progress of our plans coming along?
* '''Player:''' I'm still working on it.
* '''Awowogei:''' Don't let me down Kruk, we all know what is at stake here.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Garkor===
* '''Garkor:''' Have you learned anything from Awowogei yet?
* '''Player:''' The monkeys are planning another attack!
* '''Garkor:''' Ah, this comes as little surprise. Did you uncover any details of the plans?
* '''Player:''' The assault is coming in three stages...
* '''Player:''' First, the monkeys wish to join into an alliance with the trolls and ogres...
* '''Garkor:''' That makes sense, it's no secret that those races are no fans of humans, other than perhaps as ingredients in a soup... What else did you learn?
* '''Player:''' The monkeys have been building a fleet of battleships.
* '''Garkor:''' That is odd, we have spies posted at the shipyard who haven't reported any news of this to us. I'll get a few scouts to look into it further. What's the final element to this attack?
* '''Player:''' Apparently Kruk has been working on a secret weapon, I've got no idea what it is.
* '''Garkor:''' Well then, that sounds ominous. I'll have some men look into it. For now, let's deal with the problems we can solve.
* '''Garkor:''' You must convince the trolls and ogres not to ally with the monkeys.
* '''Player:''' Any ideas on how?
* '''Garkor:''' You should pay a visit to the military officials of each race. I believe a troll general by the name of Kob is still filling that role in the Troll Stronghold. As for the ogres, I would recommend finding the head of the city
* '''Garkor:''' guard in Gu'Tanoth.
* '''Player:''' I'll get right to it.
* {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Garkor again====
* '''Garkor:''' You must convince the trolls and ogres not to ally with the monkeys.
* '''Player:''' Any ideas on how?
